  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed retention of the first floor rear roof terrace and spiral staircase by reason of  inappropriate design, scale, massing and prominent location would form an overdominant and visually discordant feature to the rear elevation to the detriment of the character and appearance of this locally listed building, the wider terrace to which it forms part of and the Upper Street North Conservation Area.  The proposed development is therefore considered to be contrary to policy 9 of Islington's Core Strategy 2011, policies D4 (Designing in context), D11 (Alterations and extensions) D24 (Materials) of Islington’s Unitary Development Plan 2002  Upper Street North Conservation Guidance Note, and Islington’s Urban Design Guidance 2006 and PPS 5."
